1
00:00:04,843 --> 00:00:06,377
Do you have cash?

2
00:00:06,444 --> 00:00:08,480
I didn't bring any cash.

3
00:00:11,916 --> 00:00:14,552
<i>The world is full of coincidences.</i>

4
00:00:14,619 --> 00:00:16,654
You can add hers with mine.

5
00:00:18,490 --> 00:00:19,357
No, you don't have to.

6
00:00:20,492 --> 00:00:21,726
<i>Twenty years ago,</i>

7
00:00:21,793 --> 00:00:25,063
<i>I had a fateful encounter with Mariko.</i>

8
00:00:25,830 --> 00:00:28,800
<i>I've always just watched over her.</i>

9
00:00:32,871 --> 00:00:35,039
<i>But now, she is finally aware of me.</i>

10
00:00:35,773 --> 00:00:36,441
NOTICE OF TRANSFER

11
00:00:36,508 --> 00:00:38,042
<i>Coincidences can be manufactured.</i>

12
00:00:39,077 --> 00:00:41,212
<i>A coincidence meant to make Mariko smile.</i>

13
00:00:41,813 --> 00:00:43,781
That old retro-style cafe
behind the office?

14
00:00:44,482 --> 00:00:45,617
<i>However…</i>

15
00:00:46,651 --> 00:00:51,723
<i>there are plenty of people who</i>
<i>approach Mariko and those who envy her.</i>

16
00:00:54,325 --> 00:00:58,096
<i>I have evidence that you used fraud</i>
<i>to obtain that partnership.</i>

17
00:00:58,163 --> 00:00:59,564
If you don't want this exposed,

18
00:00:59,631 --> 00:01:01,432
<i>withdraw from the new project.</i>

19
00:01:01,499 --> 00:01:03,434
Please, withdraw.

20
00:01:03,501 --> 00:01:05,436
-Please!
-What is wrong with you?

21
00:01:05,503 --> 00:01:07,472
Are you crazy or something?

22
00:01:07,539 --> 00:01:08,740
-Whoa!
-Please!

23
00:01:09,707 --> 00:01:11,609
<i>I must do what I need to do.</i>

24
00:01:12,510 --> 00:01:13,444
Murder?

25
00:01:14,512 --> 00:01:16,614
<i>Because I'm the one by Mariko's side.</i>

26
00:01:16,681 --> 00:01:18,049
I'M THE ONLY ONE BY MARIKO'S SIDE

27
00:01:18,116 --> 00:01:19,150
<i>I'll protect her.</i>

28
00:01:20,185 --> 00:01:21,586
19-JUN-26

29
00:01:27,192 --> 00:01:28,860
<i>That is the one thing I won't compromise.</i>

30
00:01:33,565 --> 00:01:35,800
NOSE COSMETICS

31
00:01:44,909 --> 00:01:46,678
<i>8:23 a.m.</i>

32
00:01:50,682 --> 00:01:53,117
<i>Mariko goes to work</i>
<i>at this exact time every morning.</i>

33
00:02:22,614 --> 00:02:25,783
BRAND BUSINESS DEPARTMENT

34
00:02:29,354 --> 00:02:31,389
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

35
00:02:31,456 --> 00:02:33,825
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

36
00:02:35,927 --> 00:02:39,130
<i>The very first thing she does when she</i>
<i>arrives at work is use alcohol sanitizer.</i>

37
00:02:39,197 --> 00:02:41,366
<i>After thoroughly wiping the keyboard,</i>

38
00:02:42,934 --> 00:02:46,371
<i>she checks the day's schedule,</i>
<i>right about now.</i>

39
00:02:47,071 --> 00:02:49,207
TOKYO DEPARTMENT STORE STATUS

40
00:02:52,577 --> 00:02:53,845
<i>Once she finishes that…</i>

41
00:02:54,979 --> 00:02:55,847
Here you go.

42
00:02:56,781 --> 00:02:58,983
Thank you. I was just
thinking I wanted one.

43
00:03:07,225 --> 00:03:08,960
<i>Mariko likes café lattes.</i>

44
00:03:13,631 --> 00:03:17,268
<i>I know everything about Mariko.</i>

45
00:03:20,004 --> 00:03:20,605
PROPOSAL TO INTRODUCE AI
INTO CLOUD SERVICES

46
00:03:20,672 --> 00:03:22,807
If we introduce AI into the cloud system,

47
00:03:22,874 --> 00:03:24,309
the work required to find documents

48
00:03:24,375 --> 00:03:27,178
from our vast library
should decrease significantly.

49
00:03:27,245 --> 00:03:29,213
No, to put that into effect,

50
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:31,115
-the cost would be enormous--
-That is exactly

51
00:03:31,182 --> 00:03:32,917
the kind of thing
we should spend money on.

52
00:03:33,618 --> 00:03:34,886
If we revamp the system,

53
00:03:34,952 --> 00:03:38,256
it should reduce overtime by 40 hours
per year in each department.

54
00:03:40,091 --> 00:03:42,627
<i>That's easy for her to say.</i>

55
00:03:42,694 --> 00:03:45,129
From her standpoint, yes.

56
00:03:45,196 --> 00:03:47,432
I heard she just got
a new project approved too.

57
00:03:47,932 --> 00:03:51,235
Must be nice to have someone
backing you up.

58
00:03:58,076 --> 00:04:00,144
Don't worry about what they say.

59
00:04:02,013 --> 00:04:03,247
Oh, that.

60
00:04:03,981 --> 00:04:06,384
-I'm used to it.
-What?

61
00:04:07,218 --> 00:04:09,620
Wait, so are you still sad
about that thing?

62
00:04:11,022 --> 00:04:15,059
I never imagined dating would be harder
than college or job-hunting.

63
00:04:15,827 --> 00:04:16,994
Did something happen?

64
00:04:17,495 --> 00:04:18,996
No, nothing.

65
00:04:19,597 --> 00:04:21,866
I can't even keep a text conversation
going with anyone.

66
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:25,803
In the end, they just want to get
on good terms with my father.

67
00:04:25,870 --> 00:04:27,572
A lot of them are like that.

68
00:04:28,306 --> 00:04:31,676
So they're not actually interested in you?

69
00:04:31,743 --> 00:04:33,277
Don't put it so bluntly.

70
00:04:34,645 --> 00:04:36,247
What about that guy from the other day?

71
00:04:36,314 --> 00:04:38,883
The one your grandmother
introduced to you.

72
00:04:41,152 --> 00:04:43,154
I almost didn't come.

73
00:04:43,221 --> 00:04:44,522
But I'm glad I came.

74
00:04:45,490 --> 00:04:48,960
What about his job? What does he do?

75
00:04:49,026 --> 00:04:50,561
Uh, he's a civil servant.

76
00:04:50,628 --> 00:04:53,030
A civil servant! That's great!

77
00:04:53,097 --> 00:04:54,799
-You think so?
-Yes!

78
00:04:55,566 --> 00:04:58,336
But we have had no developments
since then, either.

79
00:04:59,904 --> 00:05:03,808
Mariko, maybe you're not taking
any initiative at all?

80
00:05:03,875 --> 00:05:07,278
Are you making an effort to show them
who you really are?

81
00:05:13,985 --> 00:05:16,788
I plan to do it…

82
00:05:17,288 --> 00:05:19,056
Don't just plan, do it!

83
00:05:25,930 --> 00:05:26,898
Hello.

84
00:05:27,965 --> 00:05:29,267
Hello.

85
00:05:32,837 --> 00:05:35,039
-Hello.
-Hey there.

86
00:05:36,974 --> 00:05:38,910
Mariko, you can make it tomorrow, right?

87
00:05:38,976 --> 00:05:41,279
To the golf session with the CEO
of Keihin Department Store.

88
00:05:41,345 --> 00:05:42,947
-Yes.
-Actually,

89
00:05:43,014 --> 00:05:44,982
I received a call from them
just a moment ago.

90
00:05:45,049 --> 00:05:46,684
It seems one of them can't make it.

91
00:05:47,785 --> 00:05:49,520
Then shall we send
another one on our side?

92
00:05:49,587 --> 00:05:50,755
Asai, can you go?

93
00:05:50,822 --> 00:05:54,292
-No, I'm not really good at golf.
-<i>Mariko started golfing after she joined.</i>

94
00:05:54,792 --> 00:05:56,727
<i>It's good for entertaining guests.</i>

95
00:05:57,829 --> 00:05:58,896
<i>Mariko always prepares</i>

96
00:05:59,597 --> 00:06:02,433
<i>so that nothing at work</i>
<i>can catch her by surprise.</i>

97
00:06:04,702 --> 00:06:07,004
You still can't contact Tateiwa?

98
00:06:08,005 --> 00:06:08,840
No.

99
00:06:10,007 --> 00:06:11,576
What's going on?

100
00:06:16,881 --> 00:06:18,382
<i>And…</i>

101
00:06:20,518 --> 00:06:22,353
<i>I have my preparations too.</i>

102
00:06:35,666 --> 00:06:37,301
NOSE COSMETICS

103
00:06:37,368 --> 00:06:39,070
Sorry for bothering you.

104
00:06:39,136 --> 00:06:42,440
I'd like to speak with
the person in charge here.

105
00:06:42,974 --> 00:06:45,743
Please wait a moment. I'll ask.

106
00:06:50,181 --> 00:06:53,084
Well then, what can we help you with?

107
00:06:54,285 --> 00:06:55,953
Last night, around 10 p.m.,

108
00:06:56,020 --> 00:06:58,422
one of your directors,
Mr. Tsuyoshi Tateiwa,

109
00:06:58,489 --> 00:06:59,857
<i>was found dead.</i>

110
00:06:59,924 --> 00:07:00,892
What?

111
00:07:01,692 --> 00:07:04,061
Was it an accident?

112
00:07:04,128 --> 00:07:06,731
The police are investigating it
as a criminal case.

113
00:07:08,299 --> 00:07:11,869
When was the last time
you contacted Mr. Tateiwa?

114
00:07:12,537 --> 00:07:14,105
Two days ago.

115
00:07:14,171 --> 00:07:18,709
Actually, we were unable
to reach him as well, and we were worried.

116
00:07:21,178 --> 00:07:25,983
By the way, did Mr. Tateiwa
have any trouble at work,

117
00:07:26,050 --> 00:07:28,686
or did anyone hold grudges against him?

118
00:07:35,693 --> 00:07:39,730
This email was sent to me
the night before yesterday.

119
00:07:39,797 --> 00:07:40,731
This is evidence

120
00:07:40,798 --> 00:07:44,402
that Tateiwa was misappropriating
company expenses and other funds.

121
00:07:44,468 --> 00:07:47,905
-Do you have any idea who the sender is?
-I do not.

122
00:07:49,473 --> 00:07:52,577
The night two days ago,
that would be when the murder occurred.

123
00:07:52,643 --> 00:07:55,346
-May we have this data?
-Yes.

124
00:07:55,913 --> 00:07:58,816
We would also like to see
Mr. Tateiwa's desk.

125
00:07:58,883 --> 00:08:00,251
-Asai.
-Yes.

126
00:08:00,318 --> 00:08:01,919
-I'll show you.
-Thank you.

127
00:08:09,527 --> 00:08:11,796
This is terrible! This is terrible! Hey!

128
00:08:13,164 --> 00:08:14,599
-The police are here!
-What?

129
00:08:14,665 --> 00:08:15,533
The police?

130
00:08:16,901 --> 00:08:17,902
They say Mr. Tateiwa

131
00:08:19,036 --> 00:08:20,204
was murdered.

132
00:08:20,705 --> 00:08:23,307
-What? What do you mean he was murdered?
-No…

133
00:08:23,374 --> 00:08:25,309
I don't know the details, but…

134
00:08:26,577 --> 00:08:29,347
Look, the detectives are here.

135
00:08:50,001 --> 00:08:51,836
<i>Last night, at around 10 p.m.,</i>

136
00:08:51,902 --> 00:08:56,707
<i>a man was found collapsed on the street</i>

137
00:08:56,774 --> 00:08:59,076
<i>and was confirmed to have passed away.</i>

138
00:09:00,044 --> 00:09:02,947
<i>The incident happened after 5:00 p.m.</i>

139
00:09:03,014 --> 00:09:05,016
<i>A passerby reported</i>

140
00:09:05,082 --> 00:09:09,787
<i>finding a man collapsed</i>
<i>on a street in Shinagawa.</i>

141
00:09:09,854 --> 00:09:14,825
<i>The victim was Mr. Tsuyoshi Tateiwa.</i>

142
00:09:14,892 --> 00:09:17,695
<i>His body had several stab wounds,</i>

143
00:09:17,762 --> 00:09:20,965
<i>and the police are investigating this</i>
<i>as a homicide.</i>

144
00:09:32,476 --> 00:09:33,611
TSUYOSHI TATEIWA

145
00:09:36,714 --> 00:09:38,082
CREATING BACKUP

146
00:09:54,231 --> 00:09:56,167
ARE YOU SURE YOU WANT TO RESET THIS PC?

147
00:09:56,233 --> 00:09:57,168
RESETTING PC…

148
00:10:01,138 --> 00:10:03,874
SATORU HATANO RELEASED FROM PRISON

149
00:10:13,818 --> 00:10:16,220
If there is anything else
you wish to investigate,

150
00:10:16,287 --> 00:10:18,022
please contact me directly.

151
00:10:18,723 --> 00:10:21,158
Understood. Thank you very much.

152
00:10:22,426 --> 00:10:23,260
Good day.

153
00:10:34,105 --> 00:10:37,041
Those incriminating documents,
sent anonymously…

154
00:10:37,108 --> 00:10:39,009
I'd bet they were sent by the killer.

155
00:11:00,698 --> 00:11:03,134
COMPANY DIRECTOR FOUND DEAD ON STREET

156
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:04,802
DEEMED HOMICIDE

157
00:11:07,571 --> 00:11:08,939
Here, this is on the house.

158
00:11:10,074 --> 00:11:13,110
You don't seem to be focusing
very well on your work today.

159
00:11:15,246 --> 00:11:16,113
Thank you very much.

160
00:11:18,015 --> 00:11:19,416
You're that guy's boss, right?

161
00:11:20,151 --> 00:11:21,519
-That guy?
-Sota Yukimura.

162
00:11:23,554 --> 00:11:24,889
Yes. Are you acquaintances?

163
00:11:24,955 --> 00:11:27,291
Yes, yes, we both
went to Futasubashi University.

164
00:11:30,694 --> 00:11:32,463
-Futasubashi, I went there too.
-Oh, here he is.

165
00:11:32,530 --> 00:11:35,232
Hey, don't say anything you don't need to.

166
00:11:35,299 --> 00:11:37,368
It's fine. She'd find out
eventually anyway.

167
00:11:37,434 --> 00:11:39,036
We were both in the Faculty of Commerce.

168
00:11:39,103 --> 00:11:40,671
I went there too!

169
00:11:40,738 --> 00:11:43,974
We both took a gap year, so we're
one academic year below you, though.

170
00:11:44,041 --> 00:11:46,510
-Oh, really?
-I've wanted to talk to you

171
00:11:46,577 --> 00:11:48,012
ever since university.

172
00:11:48,078 --> 00:11:49,980
Oh, I'm Tomoya Sagara, by the way.

173
00:11:50,047 --> 00:11:52,049
-Okay.
-Mariko, what do you think of this guy--

174
00:11:52,116 --> 00:11:53,818
That's enough.

175
00:11:53,884 --> 00:11:55,186
-What, what?
-Go back to work.

176
00:11:55,252 --> 00:11:56,720
I'm going, all right, all right.

177
00:11:57,855 --> 00:12:00,291
I get it, okay? Want a cookie?

178
00:12:00,357 --> 00:12:01,592
No.

179
00:12:12,069 --> 00:12:14,205
Don't be mad. I said I was sorry.

180
00:12:15,172 --> 00:12:17,374
I was trying to be your wingman,

181
00:12:17,441 --> 00:12:19,376
giving you two a chance
to get to know each other.

182
00:12:19,443 --> 00:12:21,745
Look, consider this an apology.

183
00:12:21,812 --> 00:12:24,682
You liar. Bet you just talked
and couldn't stop.

184
00:12:26,283 --> 00:12:27,718
It's fine.

185
00:12:27,785 --> 00:12:30,821
I know what's okay to say and what's not.

186
00:12:33,290 --> 00:12:35,559
If I told her you've loved her
for 25 years straight,

187
00:12:35,626 --> 00:12:37,595
she'd find it creepy
and reject you instantly.

188
00:12:37,661 --> 00:12:39,463
I would absolutely never say that.

189
00:12:43,467 --> 00:12:45,536
Don't worry.

190
00:12:46,303 --> 00:12:49,707
I won't steal your one and only love.

191
00:12:49,773 --> 00:12:51,842
What? Mariko wouldn't
fall for you, Tomoya.

192
00:12:51,909 --> 00:12:54,945
What's that about? You don't know that.

193
00:12:55,012 --> 00:12:57,047
I know everything about Mariko.

194
00:12:58,415 --> 00:12:59,950
Everything, huh…

195
00:13:01,285 --> 00:13:05,289
Well then, do you know
who Mariko's closest friend is?

196
00:13:05,356 --> 00:13:06,590
Her colleague and secretary, Izumi.

197
00:13:06,657 --> 00:13:07,491
That was fast.

198
00:13:09,193 --> 00:13:11,562
Izumi is a senior colleague
three years older than Mariko,

199
00:13:11,629 --> 00:13:15,299
but since Mariko is the manager,
she is her most trusted subordinate.

200
00:13:16,367 --> 00:13:18,302
While they have
a professional relationship,

201
00:13:18,869 --> 00:13:22,840
she is a rare, friend-like figure
with whom Mariko can be herself.

202
00:13:23,507 --> 00:13:26,410
Then what about outside of work?

203
00:13:26,477 --> 00:13:28,913
Like how she spends
long holidays and stuff.

204
00:13:30,414 --> 00:13:33,984
Mariko doesn't take much paid leave…

205
00:13:35,586 --> 00:13:38,322
Oh, but for New Year's, she spent it
in London with her grandmother.

206
00:13:39,590 --> 00:13:42,426
You could see fireworks
from the Thames River cruise.

207
00:13:42,493 --> 00:13:44,028
They were beautiful.

208
00:13:45,329 --> 00:13:46,563
Did you go too…

209
00:13:48,933 --> 00:13:50,567
No, never mind.

210
00:13:52,169 --> 00:13:54,138
I don't really want to know. It's scary.

211
00:13:55,639 --> 00:13:59,944
When it comes to Mariko, I know
everything, and I understand everything.

212
00:14:02,179 --> 00:14:03,380
I wonder.

213
00:14:04,682 --> 00:14:08,252
-What?
-This all sounds very one-sided to me.

214
00:14:08,319 --> 00:14:09,620
Would she really date you?

215
00:14:10,721 --> 00:14:12,056
What?

216
00:14:12,556 --> 00:14:15,359
-I'm not planning on--
-And what's that you've been doing?

217
00:14:17,795 --> 00:14:18,963
Golf?

218
00:14:23,267 --> 00:14:25,402
MARIKO

219
00:14:31,241 --> 00:14:33,510
Nice shot!

220
00:14:33,577 --> 00:14:34,945
Nice shot!

221
00:14:35,746 --> 00:14:39,083
-Sent it flying, like always!
-All right!

222
00:14:54,331 --> 00:14:57,735
-Nice shot!
-Your direction is perfect!

223
00:14:57,801 --> 00:14:58,869
Thank you very much.

224
00:14:59,770 --> 00:15:01,105
Do you have a professional coach?

225
00:15:01,171 --> 00:15:03,140
I went to a place called Koto Golf Club.

226
00:15:04,375 --> 00:15:06,010
I used to go there too.

227
00:15:06,076 --> 00:15:08,979
Oh, it's nice there, isn't it?
It's close to the company,

228
00:15:09,046 --> 00:15:10,781
and they offer cheap personal lessons.

229
00:15:11,582 --> 00:15:12,883
That's true.

230
00:15:15,085 --> 00:15:18,822
Man, where do you train, Jinno?

231
00:15:21,492 --> 00:15:24,028
Sorry for asking you
to come on such short notice.

232
00:15:24,561 --> 00:15:27,998
No one else in our department
could play golf, so it was a huge help.

233
00:15:28,065 --> 00:15:29,133
Not at all.

234
00:15:31,335 --> 00:15:32,870
Do you play often?

235
00:15:33,604 --> 00:15:36,807
I often go to the driving range
at Koto Golf Club.

236
00:15:38,208 --> 00:15:41,111
<i>I wonder if a lot of people</i>
<i>from our company go there?</i>

237
00:15:41,645 --> 00:15:43,781
<i>That might be the case.</i>

238
00:15:50,621 --> 00:15:52,356
<i>Playing golf with Mariko…</i>

239
00:15:53,724 --> 00:15:56,326
<i>To think such a day would come.</i>

240
00:15:57,728 --> 00:16:00,764
<i>Am I about to be called to heaven? No,</i>

241
00:16:01,865 --> 00:16:03,801
<i>perhaps I have already been called.</i>

242
00:16:06,203 --> 00:16:07,805
<i>This is heaven.</i>

243
00:16:15,412 --> 00:16:17,648
Nice shot!

244
00:16:29,893 --> 00:16:32,796
I think this one would be better.

245
00:16:34,331 --> 00:16:35,299
Thank you.

246
00:16:48,879 --> 00:16:51,081
-Nice one!
-Nice one!

247
00:17:00,991 --> 00:17:04,061
<i>To think such a day would come…</i>

248
00:17:07,498 --> 00:17:10,134
Isn't your company
having it rough right now?

249
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:12,803
You know, with that director,
Tateiwa, was it?

250
00:17:12,870 --> 00:17:14,471
Yes.

251
00:17:14,538 --> 00:17:18,108
We pulled some strings to keep
the company name out of the news for now.

252
00:17:19,009 --> 00:17:22,613
Well, the weekly magazines
will probably find out eventually, though.

253
00:17:22,679 --> 00:17:24,348
Well,

254
00:17:24,414 --> 00:17:27,851
a murder case is no laughing matter.

255
00:17:27,918 --> 00:17:31,388
It'd be terrifying if the killer
turned out to be someone close to him.

256
00:17:36,026 --> 00:17:37,194
Yes, exactly.

257
00:17:37,261 --> 00:17:40,998
Thankfully, our brand for young people
called VELEL is performing well.

258
00:17:41,064 --> 00:17:43,333
I know. I saw an article saying that

259
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:46,303
while the industry as a whole
is struggling to establish brand loyalty,

260
00:17:46,370 --> 00:17:49,540
VELEL has maintained
an upward trend since its release.

261
00:17:51,408 --> 00:17:52,943
Actually, it has been decided

262
00:17:53,010 --> 00:17:56,113
that we will be launching
a new skincare line from VELEL.

263
00:17:56,647 --> 00:18:00,217
We would be very grateful to have
your support, Jinno.

264
00:18:00,284 --> 00:18:03,120
Shall we set up
an independent counter at our place?

265
00:18:03,754 --> 00:18:05,455
Yes, please!

266
00:18:06,557 --> 00:18:10,160
Your father and I
have been friends for over half a century,

267
00:18:10,227 --> 00:18:13,797
so our department store
will give you full support.

268
00:18:13,864 --> 00:18:14,898
Thank you very much.

269
00:18:15,399 --> 00:18:18,068
My, how impressive, how impressive.

270
00:18:19,169 --> 00:18:22,306
Nose Cosmetics is secure
with such a splendid successor.

271
00:18:22,372 --> 00:18:23,207
Well,

272
00:18:23,273 --> 00:18:26,043
I only made her a director
because she's my daughter.

273
00:18:26,109 --> 00:18:27,110
She still has a long way to go.

274
00:18:32,783 --> 00:18:36,386
You've known each other for over 50 years.
What relationship do you have?

275
00:18:36,453 --> 00:18:39,656
We're in a Gin-chan,
Jin-chan kind of friendship.

276
00:18:40,457 --> 00:18:41,858
That's right.

277
00:18:41,925 --> 00:18:45,195
I didn't think Jin-chan
would rise this high, though.

278
00:18:45,262 --> 00:18:46,863
Well, I'm glad we stayed on good terms.

279
00:18:46,930 --> 00:18:48,465
The feeling is mutual.

280
00:18:53,070 --> 00:18:54,738
Just this way.

281
00:18:55,472 --> 00:18:58,642
You did great, Jin-chan.

282
00:19:00,611 --> 00:19:02,579
-Thank you for today.
-Likewise.

283
00:19:08,819 --> 00:19:12,756
Great work. Thank you for today.
Let's meet again.

284
00:19:13,824 --> 00:19:15,792
Yes. Thank you very much.

285
00:19:15,859 --> 00:19:18,228
-Well then, I'll be leaving.
-Okay.

286
00:19:18,295 --> 00:19:19,129
See you.

287
00:19:25,636 --> 00:19:26,903
Yukimura, I'll give you a ride.

288
00:19:30,240 --> 00:19:31,074
What?

289
00:19:58,101 --> 00:19:59,136
You must be tired, right?

290
00:19:59,703 --> 00:20:02,472
-Sorry, I know it's your day off.
-No, no.

291
00:20:02,539 --> 00:20:03,607
That's not why.

292
00:20:16,053 --> 00:20:19,089
At what age did you start drinking coffee?

293
00:20:20,457 --> 00:20:22,459
That was a boring question. Sorry.

294
00:20:23,994 --> 00:20:25,195
Um…

295
00:20:26,196 --> 00:20:27,898
I think it was in elementary school?

296
00:20:28,799 --> 00:20:32,736
I think I snuck a sip of what
my mother was drinking.

297
00:20:34,805 --> 00:20:38,608
Oh, but I didn't start liking it
until I became an adult.

298
00:20:38,675 --> 00:20:40,477
-I like cafes, so that's why.
-Oh,

299
00:20:40,544 --> 00:20:42,112
I like cafes too.

300
00:20:42,879 --> 00:20:44,881
Um, I like how you're in the same space,

301
00:20:44,948 --> 00:20:48,385
but it feels like everyone
is in their own world.

302
00:20:49,953 --> 00:20:52,289
-I get that. I feel the same way.
-Oh?

303
00:20:53,457 --> 00:20:54,324
You do?

304
00:20:55,292 --> 00:20:57,527
Well, ever since I was a kid,

305
00:20:58,095 --> 00:21:00,330
I've liked looking at apartment buildings
from a distance.

306
00:21:00,897 --> 00:21:02,099
Apartment buildings?

307
00:21:02,165 --> 00:21:05,502
When those concrete-enclosed boxes
are born into this world,

308
00:21:05,569 --> 00:21:10,307
people who were living separate lives
fit neatly and politely into them.

309
00:21:10,374 --> 00:21:13,677
In that collective nature,
I felt a kind of beauty.

310
00:21:13,744 --> 00:21:15,912
That same feeling
is packed into cafes too.

311
00:21:16,613 --> 00:21:19,282
No one knows each other,

312
00:21:19,349 --> 00:21:21,151
but in the way that everyone

313
00:21:21,651 --> 00:21:24,721
gathers in a single space
and quietly shares time together,

314
00:21:25,722 --> 00:21:27,491
I feel a sense of romance.

315
00:21:32,028 --> 00:21:33,296
I'm talking too much, aren't I?

316
00:21:34,531 --> 00:21:36,133
I don't mind.

317
00:21:42,839 --> 00:21:43,840
Sorry.

318
00:21:48,845 --> 00:21:50,480
We surprisingly have a lot in common.

319
00:21:51,948 --> 00:21:52,883
Same university, too.

320
00:21:54,050 --> 00:21:59,189
Yes, uh, well, I barely managed
to slip in after a gap year.

321
00:22:00,090 --> 00:22:01,691
I barely got in too.

322
00:22:03,326 --> 00:22:06,430
But for some reason,
I've had a lucky life.

323
00:22:08,198 --> 00:22:11,568
Even on the day of the entrance exam,
I messed up,

324
00:22:12,135 --> 00:22:13,570
but I got lucky and passed.

325
00:22:13,637 --> 00:22:15,205
I don't think it was luck.

326
00:22:15,739 --> 00:22:19,109
You studied so hard.
It was your own ability.

327
00:22:20,210 --> 00:22:24,281
I mean, you just lost
your exam admission ticket.

328
00:22:24,347 --> 00:22:25,816
It doesn't mean you'd fail, right?

329
00:22:28,485 --> 00:22:30,520
What? Did I mention a ticket?

330
00:22:34,391 --> 00:22:35,325
No, uh…

331
00:22:37,627 --> 00:22:39,463
I just figured, messing up on exam day

332
00:22:40,063 --> 00:22:43,767
would mean losing
or dropping your exam ticket.

333
00:22:46,369 --> 00:22:47,337
Oh, okay.

334
00:22:56,746 --> 00:22:58,515
In other words, what I wanted to say

335
00:22:59,683 --> 00:23:01,485
is that both university
and your current job

336
00:23:02,953 --> 00:23:05,322
are results you grabbed
through real effort…

337
00:23:07,624 --> 00:23:09,392
and not luck at all.

338
00:23:12,028 --> 00:23:14,064
Sorry for speaking like I know everything.

339
00:23:16,132 --> 00:23:18,468
Everyone else says differently, though.

340
00:23:20,570 --> 00:23:23,740
Well, I only get to see clients
because my father is backing me up.

341
00:23:23,807 --> 00:23:25,308
So I don't blame them.

342
00:23:30,680 --> 00:23:32,549
I wonder why I'm telling you this.

343
00:23:33,216 --> 00:23:34,050
It's fine.

344
00:23:54,671 --> 00:23:56,273
<i>July 25th.</i>

345
00:23:56,973 --> 00:24:00,911
<i>Today, several things that should</i>
<i>have been impossible, no,</i>

346
00:24:01,711 --> 00:24:05,382
<i>things I've always waited for,</i>
<i>have finally happened.</i>

347
00:24:14,591 --> 00:24:15,759
JULY 25

348
00:24:15,825 --> 00:24:19,162
<i>It makes me realize</i>
<i>that life is connected.</i>

349
00:24:20,130 --> 00:24:23,466
<i>Because I started playing golf back then,</i>

350
00:24:23,533 --> 00:24:27,070
<i>it led to me being invited</i>
<i>to the client game today.</i>

351
00:24:33,910 --> 00:24:35,412
MARIKO

352
00:24:35,478 --> 00:24:38,515
FIRST TIME PLAYING GOLF IN A WHILE
THE WEATHER WAS GREAT

353
00:24:43,887 --> 00:24:44,821
<i>But…</i>

354
00:24:49,693 --> 00:24:52,462
<i>if life is connected…</i>

355
00:24:52,963 --> 00:24:54,364
JAPONICA WORKBOOK

356
00:24:55,465 --> 00:24:56,766
<i>…then it's possible…</i>

357
00:24:58,234 --> 00:25:00,203
<i>that the past will catch up with you.</i>

358
00:25:03,239 --> 00:25:04,274
<i>Today,</i>

359
00:25:05,241 --> 00:25:07,510
<i>I overheard something outrageous.</i>

360
00:25:07,577 --> 00:25:10,580
You got me good today, Jin-chan!

361
00:25:10,647 --> 00:25:11,948
Oh, by the way,

362
00:25:12,549 --> 00:25:14,851
I heard Hatano was released
from prison, right?

363
00:25:15,885 --> 00:25:16,786
Yes…

364
00:25:16,853 --> 00:25:20,023
Him, kidnapping someone…

365
00:25:20,090 --> 00:25:21,591
I still can't believe it.

366
00:25:22,792 --> 00:25:25,228
It looks like he's telling the weekly mags
lots of things.

367
00:25:25,795 --> 00:25:26,730
Be careful.

368
00:25:27,263 --> 00:25:30,033
It was a long time ago, but he might talk
about you too.

369
00:25:33,003 --> 00:25:34,938
<i>This man named Hatano…</i>

370
00:25:35,005 --> 00:25:36,006
SERIAL KIDNAPPER, 1 DEATH

371
00:25:41,044 --> 00:25:43,480
Somebody! Somebody help!

372
00:25:43,546 --> 00:25:46,416
-<i>Though Mariko's kidnapping was thwarted,</i>
-No! No!

373
00:25:47,751 --> 00:25:50,053
<i>he kidnapped five other children</i>

374
00:25:50,587 --> 00:25:54,090
<i>and murdered one who tried to escape.</i>

375
00:25:54,157 --> 00:25:55,692
WEAPON CONFISCATED AT HOME

376
00:25:55,759 --> 00:25:56,793
HATANO SENTENCED TO 25 YEARS

377
00:25:56,860 --> 00:26:00,363
<i>It was reported that</i>
<i>he stated he targeted children</i>

378
00:26:00,430 --> 00:26:01,998
<i>of wealthy families,</i>

379
00:26:02,499 --> 00:26:03,333
GINJIRO NOSE

380
00:26:03,400 --> 00:26:07,537
<i>but Mariko's father and the kidnapper</i>
<i>were originally acquaintances.</i>

381
00:26:09,105 --> 00:26:11,975
<i>That shouldn't have been</i>
<i>written anywhere, and yet…</i>

382
00:26:13,677 --> 00:26:15,712
The President covered it up?

383
00:26:21,418 --> 00:26:22,986
WHY AN INDEPENDENT COUNTER AT KEIHIN?

384
00:26:30,160 --> 00:26:33,630
EXCLUSIVE INTERVIEW WITH SATORU HATANO
SERIAL KIDNAPPER RELEASED AFTER 25 YEARS

385
00:26:49,179 --> 00:26:51,247
THE DECIDING POINT IN THE GAME

386
00:26:55,351 --> 00:26:56,686
Eight, huh?

387
00:27:03,059 --> 00:27:05,995
MAN FOUND DEAD ON STREET IN SHINAGAWA

388
00:27:07,063 --> 00:27:07,897
NOSE COSMETICS

389
00:27:07,964 --> 00:27:09,466
I'm from Drip &amp; Note.

390
00:27:09,532 --> 00:27:12,535
-Right this way.
-Thank you.

391
00:27:25,448 --> 00:27:26,382
Excuse me.

392
00:27:27,650 --> 00:27:29,252
Have we met somewhere before?

393
00:27:30,487 --> 00:27:32,188
Ah, sorry, sorry.

394
00:27:32,255 --> 00:27:34,324
Not trying to flirt, really.

395
00:27:44,501 --> 00:27:45,502
Um…

396
00:27:46,736 --> 00:27:47,771
Do you need something?

397
00:27:49,305 --> 00:27:50,840
There's something stuck there…

398
00:27:53,576 --> 00:27:54,811
Thank you.

399
00:27:55,578 --> 00:27:56,646
It's cute, though.

400
00:28:03,219 --> 00:28:06,189
What? Yukimura went golfing
with the president?

401
00:28:06,256 --> 00:28:07,123
Yes.

402
00:28:07,190 --> 00:28:10,326
The president was very pleased.
He said he was really good and attentive.

403
00:28:11,594 --> 00:28:13,496
That's surprising for Yukimura.

404
00:28:13,563 --> 00:28:16,099
He seems quiet. So he's on "that side".

405
00:28:17,233 --> 00:28:18,201
What do you mean, "that side"?

406
00:28:18,868 --> 00:28:21,137
The side that thinks
about promotions and stuff.

407
00:28:21,204 --> 00:28:25,175
It's not so easy for an ordinary employee
to get into the president's good graces.

408
00:28:25,241 --> 00:28:28,745
So, he got in through golf. I see, I see.

409
00:28:28,812 --> 00:28:30,880
Why don't you do golf too then, Sano?

410
00:28:30,947 --> 00:28:34,350
What? I have no interest in golf.
Promotions are a hassle anyway.

411
00:28:34,417 --> 00:28:36,286
What's with you?

412
00:28:37,387 --> 00:28:38,721
I mean, it's tough, right?

413
00:28:43,560 --> 00:28:44,761
Manager? Is something wrong?

414
00:28:46,029 --> 00:28:47,063
Nothing.

415
00:28:52,235 --> 00:28:53,937
Ah, let me get that.

416
00:28:57,674 --> 00:28:58,608
Thanks.

417
00:29:04,080 --> 00:29:07,417
-Hello.
-Hello.

418
00:29:16,860 --> 00:29:18,962
Did something happen with Mariko?

419
00:29:21,397 --> 00:29:22,699
I don't know.

420
00:30:07,610 --> 00:30:08,578
I'm sorry.

421
00:30:09,679 --> 00:30:10,580
I'm Sakura.

422
00:30:11,080 --> 00:30:13,149
Um, we met the other day.

423
00:30:16,452 --> 00:30:18,688
-I'm sorry.
-No, no.

424
00:30:19,656 --> 00:30:23,426
I didn't mean to startle you.

425
00:30:24,661 --> 00:30:25,495
It's fine…

426
00:30:26,095 --> 00:30:28,264
I scared you the other day too, didn't I?

427
00:30:30,199 --> 00:30:32,302
You were that detective, right?

428
00:30:32,936 --> 00:30:33,770
Yes.

429
00:30:34,837 --> 00:30:37,473
I was too vague,
saying I'm a civil servant.

430
00:30:38,007 --> 00:30:39,208
I'm sorry.

431
00:30:40,843 --> 00:30:44,814
Of course you can't reveal everything
to someone you just met.

432
00:30:49,786 --> 00:30:50,887
Um…

433
00:30:52,789 --> 00:30:54,290
Can we start over?

434
00:31:02,999 --> 00:31:05,068
My name is Taisuke Sakura.

435
00:31:06,803 --> 00:31:11,240
I work at the Metropolitan
Police Department, Division One.

436
00:31:13,977 --> 00:31:15,411
Twenty years of service.

437
00:31:17,246 --> 00:31:18,114
I am single.

438
00:31:20,750 --> 00:31:23,219
I was hoping to deepen

439
00:31:23,920 --> 00:31:26,422
my acquaintance with you,
Mariko, in my private life.

440
00:31:28,524 --> 00:31:29,592
If you'd like,

441
00:31:30,326 --> 00:31:32,695
how about we have
a meal together sometime?

442
00:32:13,169 --> 00:32:14,003
What?

443
00:32:14,070 --> 00:32:16,239
That's not what we agreed on!

444
00:32:16,839 --> 00:32:17,840
I want our brand to be placed

445
00:32:17,907 --> 00:32:20,877
at an independent counter
at Keihin Department Store.

446
00:32:20,943 --> 00:32:24,247
If it's lumped together with Nose Brand
counters, we'll take customers from--

447
00:32:24,313 --> 00:32:27,050
It's not a bad thing
for the company as a whole.

448
00:32:28,584 --> 00:32:32,488
It will also help acquire
new customers for the existing brands.

449
00:32:32,555 --> 00:32:36,292
VELEL has a different target demographic
from our other brands.

450
00:32:36,359 --> 00:32:38,327
If they are placed side by side,

451
00:32:38,394 --> 00:32:40,530
our brand image will be indecisive!

452
00:32:41,364 --> 00:32:44,000
I cannot give you special treatment.

453
00:32:45,101 --> 00:32:46,369
Special treatment?

454
00:32:52,475 --> 00:32:56,546
Did this project pass
because I'm the president's daughter?

455
00:33:02,919 --> 00:33:06,022
This project passed
because I'm the president's daughter.

456
00:33:06,089 --> 00:33:07,790
I became manager
because I'm your daughter.

457
00:33:07,857 --> 00:33:10,259
I only got into this company
because I'm your daughter.

458
00:33:13,229 --> 00:33:16,899
And because I'm your daughter,
I got kidnapped.

459
00:33:48,164 --> 00:33:49,966
Mariko may be the president's daughter,

460
00:33:50,032 --> 00:33:52,168
but she isn't relying
on special treatment.

461
00:33:55,204 --> 00:33:57,306
Mariko has been fighting forever.

462
00:33:58,774 --> 00:34:00,109
<i>Mariko, hold on.</i>

463
00:34:00,176 --> 00:34:01,277
Wait.

464
00:34:02,712 --> 00:34:04,013
I'll be fine by myself.

465
00:34:04,547 --> 00:34:06,115
The culprit has been caught.

466
00:34:06,182 --> 00:34:08,050
-But…
-I'm off.

467
00:34:09,452 --> 00:34:10,653
Mariko…

468
00:34:19,495 --> 00:34:21,831
Even though she must have been hurt a lot…

469
00:34:24,433 --> 00:34:26,068
she always looked forward…

470
00:34:28,337 --> 00:34:30,206
<i>and fought with her own strength.</i>

471
00:34:34,911 --> 00:34:36,646
It has nothing to do with being
the president's daughter.

472
00:34:36,712 --> 00:34:38,681
Mariko is Mariko…

473
00:34:40,483 --> 00:34:42,251
Nobody understands.

474
00:34:47,089 --> 00:34:49,458
Because I know the real Mariko.

475
00:34:49,525 --> 00:34:52,695
So what if you do?

476
00:34:55,231 --> 00:34:57,567
Just knowing doesn't
change anything, does it?

477
00:34:59,769 --> 00:35:01,571
What do you want to do?

478
00:35:04,273 --> 00:35:05,942
You've loved her for 25 years,

479
00:35:06,008 --> 00:35:07,843
but never had the courage to talk to her.

480
00:35:07,910 --> 00:35:09,412
You've just always watched.

481
00:35:09,478 --> 00:35:12,481
Now you've finally talked to her,
and she's aware of you, right?

482
00:35:18,487 --> 00:35:20,022
So what next?

483
00:36:22,752 --> 00:36:25,054
COSMETICS INGREDIENT GUIDELINE

484
00:36:30,326 --> 00:36:32,728
VELEL SKINCARE - SEPARATE PR CAMPAIGN

485
00:36:32,795 --> 00:36:34,330
SOCIAL MEDIA MARKETING

486
00:36:34,397 --> 00:36:35,998
CHANCE OF SUCCESS, HIGH

487
00:36:39,702 --> 00:36:40,569
Sorry.

488
00:36:42,471 --> 00:36:43,472
This is…

489
00:36:46,409 --> 00:36:49,945
Um, uh, well…

490
00:36:50,012 --> 00:36:52,615
It would be great if we could have

491
00:36:52,682 --> 00:36:55,351
an independent counter
at Keihin Department Store,

492
00:36:55,418 --> 00:36:56,786
but I realized that

493
00:36:56,852 --> 00:37:00,523
we didn't originally think up
the PR plan based on that assumption.

494
00:37:01,490 --> 00:37:04,460
So I looked into

495
00:37:04,527 --> 00:37:09,632
the PR methods used by
hit products in recent years.

496
00:37:09,699 --> 00:37:12,101
EXPERIENCE BOOTH AT TRAIN STATIONS

497
00:37:12,168 --> 00:37:14,637
If we use a selling method
that goes against our intentions

498
00:37:14,704 --> 00:37:19,608
and causes the concept of VELEL
to be conveyed incorrectly to the world,

499
00:37:20,443 --> 00:37:22,912
taking a slow and steady approach

500
00:37:24,013 --> 00:37:26,215
might be the better option.

501
00:37:29,352 --> 00:37:33,589
Ah, but it would mean going
against the president's wishes,

502
00:37:33,656 --> 00:37:36,325
so that might cause trouble
for you, Manager…

503
00:37:41,330 --> 00:37:43,299
I misunderstood you.

504
00:37:45,601 --> 00:37:47,370
I thought you

505
00:37:47,436 --> 00:37:50,506
just wanted my father to like you
to advance your career.

506
00:37:51,974 --> 00:37:56,112
That's why you were working hard
in this department and being nice to me.

507
00:37:59,849 --> 00:38:00,750
But…

508
00:38:02,184 --> 00:38:05,688
you actually have pure intentions.

509
00:38:07,256 --> 00:38:11,193
I'm the one
who assumed everyone only cares about me

510
00:38:12,428 --> 00:38:14,430
because I'm the president's daughter.

511
00:38:16,031 --> 00:38:18,834
I failed to actually look at you
as a person.

512
00:38:21,003 --> 00:38:22,071
I'm sorry.

513
00:38:27,610 --> 00:38:30,613
Actually, I was thinking
the exact same thing.

514
00:38:31,313 --> 00:38:33,048
A PR method suited for VELEL…

515
00:38:33,115 --> 00:38:35,151
I want to help!

516
00:38:38,154 --> 00:38:39,588
I want to help

517
00:38:41,023 --> 00:38:42,691
and be by your side, Manager.

518
00:38:44,760 --> 00:38:48,264
I'm so surprised that a time
like this would come in my life,

519
00:38:48,330 --> 00:38:50,833
and it's so unbelievable,

520
00:38:50,900 --> 00:38:54,403
but I'm happy just to be here right now.

521
00:38:56,739 --> 00:38:59,074
That's why I want to work hard.

522
00:39:00,342 --> 00:39:01,844
Being able to be here

523
00:39:01,911 --> 00:39:04,547
makes me the happiest
I've ever been in my life.

524
00:39:07,650 --> 00:39:09,084
What…

525
00:39:09,151 --> 00:39:11,353
"Happiest in your life"?
What an exaggeration…

526
00:39:17,526 --> 00:39:18,461
But…

527
00:39:21,797 --> 00:39:22,698
Thank you.

528
00:39:43,185 --> 00:39:45,654
<i>I want to be of use to Mariko.</i>

529
00:39:46,589 --> 00:39:50,426
<i>Just so that Mariko can live pleasantly</i>
<i>and happily.</i>

530
00:39:51,460 --> 00:39:52,695
<i>That's all.</i>

531
00:39:53,729 --> 00:39:55,264
UNIVERSITY ENTRANCE EXAM SITE

532
00:39:55,331 --> 00:39:56,165
<i>That's all I want.</i>

533
00:40:12,581 --> 00:40:14,750
ENTRANCE EXAM ADMISSION TICKET

534
00:40:26,962 --> 00:40:28,030
Hey, you!

535
00:40:28,831 --> 00:40:30,766
You dropped this.

536
00:40:32,067 --> 00:40:33,536
Thank you very much.

537
00:40:57,226 --> 00:41:00,529
<i>I want to be of use to Mariko.</i>

538
00:41:03,699 --> 00:41:06,135
GINJIRO NOSE

539
00:41:08,070 --> 00:41:09,939
GINJIRO NOSE

540
00:41:12,641 --> 00:41:13,609
HIDEO JINNO

541
00:41:13,676 --> 00:41:16,712
<i>These two have been together</i>
<i>for more than half a century,</i>

542
00:41:16,779 --> 00:41:18,380
<i>but they both went</i>

543
00:41:18,447 --> 00:41:20,249
<i>to different high schools</i>
<i>and universities.</i>

544
00:41:21,684 --> 00:41:24,219
<i>Which means, they go back</i>
<i>further than that…</i>

545
00:41:27,022 --> 00:41:28,824
HIDEO JINNO

546
00:41:28,891 --> 00:41:30,159
HIDEO JINNO

547
00:41:30,225 --> 00:41:31,660
SEE ALL PHOTOS

548
00:41:36,999 --> 00:41:38,434
WITH GIN-CHAN IN OUR OLD HANGOUT
FIRST TIME IN A WHILE!

549
00:41:41,203 --> 00:41:42,338
HOSEN

550
00:41:49,979 --> 00:41:52,548
-Thank you!
-See you!

551
00:41:52,615 --> 00:41:54,516
-Take care! Thank you!
-Thank you!

552
00:41:56,385 --> 00:41:57,286
All right.

553
00:41:57,886 --> 00:42:00,055
All right, all right.

554
00:42:03,025 --> 00:42:04,660
Excuse me.

555
00:42:04,727 --> 00:42:05,661
Yes?

556
00:42:06,862 --> 00:42:08,497
This is all I have…

557
00:42:08,564 --> 00:42:10,866
Wow, thank you so much.

558
00:42:10,933 --> 00:42:15,270
I had no idea Nose's son
had grown this big.

559
00:42:15,904 --> 00:42:18,207
And you're planning
a surprise celebration?

560
00:42:18,273 --> 00:42:19,475
He'd be so happy!

561
00:42:20,342 --> 00:42:23,078
I wonder if I have
anything else interesting?

562
00:42:23,145 --> 00:42:24,179
Wait there a second!

563
00:42:24,246 --> 00:42:26,882
Oh, thank you so much.

564
00:42:27,383 --> 00:42:29,485
YEAR 6, CLASS ONE - FRIENDS FOREVER

565
00:42:33,756 --> 00:42:36,025
HIDEO JINNO

566
00:42:36,091 --> 00:42:39,595
GINJIRO NOSE

567
00:42:41,897 --> 00:42:43,732
YEAR 6, CLASS 2
SEE YOU AGAIN AT THE GRADUATION PARTY

568
00:42:45,634 --> 00:42:47,469
YEAR 6, CLASS 3
NO. 1 GOLD STAR CLASS

569
00:42:51,340 --> 00:42:52,174
Satoru…

570
00:42:52,241 --> 00:42:54,977
SATORU HATANO

571
00:42:56,345 --> 00:42:59,114
<i>Mariko's kidnapping was not a coincidence.</i>

572
00:43:21,904 --> 00:43:24,740
<i>I won't forgive anyone who jeopardizes…</i>

573
00:43:26,375 --> 00:43:27,309
<i>Mariko's happiness.</i>

574
00:43:34,416 --> 00:43:36,952
METROPOLITAN POLICE

575
00:43:46,729 --> 00:43:51,066
It's strange that the camera
has one blind spot

576
00:43:51,133 --> 00:43:52,801
exactly where the crime scene is.

577
00:43:56,371 --> 00:43:57,206
Hey, look.

578
00:43:58,207 --> 00:44:00,542
This is right in front of the crime scene.

579
00:44:02,211 --> 00:44:04,313
Taken right before
the estimated time of death.

580
00:44:10,385 --> 00:44:11,620
Who is this man?

581
00:44:27,770 --> 00:44:28,604
Excuse me.

582
00:44:30,172 --> 00:44:31,940
You're Sota Yukimura, right?

583
00:44:34,710 --> 00:44:37,813
May I speak with you for a moment?

584
00:44:43,252 --> 00:44:45,687
<i>I want Mariko to be happy.</i>

585
00:44:46,989 --> 00:44:48,290
<i>That's all.</i>

586
00:44:53,829 --> 00:44:55,397
<i>So,</i>

587
00:44:59,134 --> 00:45:00,969
<i>you don't need to know anything.</i>

588
00:45:01,637 --> 00:45:03,505
NEXT TIME…

589
00:45:05,073 --> 00:45:08,010
Subtitle translation by: Maslin Friedman

